it is that you’re going through.

1202
00:56:16.457 --> 00:56:18.209
(others murmur quietly)

1203
00:56:18.292 --> 00:56:19.794
WOMAN: You know.
I was always one of these people

1204
00:56:19.877 --> 00:56:23.255
that could not tell the truth.

1205
00:56:23.339 --> 00:56:26.258
especially if it was painful

1206
00:56:26.342 --> 00:56:31.597
or I had to put on this façade
that I was this strong woman.

1207
00:56:31.680 --> 00:56:34.809
and inside I was
just. like. breaking up.

1208
00:56:34.892 --> 00:56:37.603
like this big hole
was inside of me.

1209
00:56:37.686 --> 00:56:42.399
And I was like. "Damn. when-when
is this ever going to change?"

1210
00:56:42.483 --> 00:56:47.321
And that part when she said.
"You don’t have to fake it."

1211
00:56:47.404 --> 00:56:50.282
I was like. "Oh. you don’t?"

1212
00:56:50.366 --> 00:56:53.619
Like. you really
could be authentic.

1213
00:56:53.702 --> 00:56:54.995
MAN:
Mm.

1214
00:56:55.079 --> 00:56:57.123
-I love her so much.
-WOMAN: Me. too.

1215
00:56:57.206 --> 00:57:00.459
MAN:
When I was. like. 13. 14.

1216
00:57:00.543 --> 00:57:03.963
those songs like "My Life."
you know. held me together.

1217
00:57:04.046 --> 00:57:05.798
-WOMAN: Yes.
-And...

1218
00:57:05.881 --> 00:57:08.008
I was going through a lot.
you know.

1219
00:57:08.092 --> 00:57:10.136
Like. why would a kid
be going through a lot?

1220
00:57:10.219 --> 00:57:11.762
Well. I was going through
a lot of--

1221
00:57:11.846 --> 00:57:14.932
I went through a lot of trauma
growing up. a lot of abuse.

1222
00:57:15.015 --> 00:57:17.017
So...

1223
00:57:17.101 --> 00:57:18.894
it...

1224
00:57:18.978 --> 00:57:22.565
The-the song "My Life"
in particular made...

1225
00:57:22.648 --> 00:57:24.692
for the first time in my life.
made me feel like

1226
00:57:24.775 --> 00:57:26.569
I could relate to somebody.

1227
00:57:26.652 --> 00:57:28.737
And...

1228
00:57:28.821 --> 00:57:31.907
I also want to share that.
at one point in my life--

1229
00:57:31.991 --> 00:57:35.619
I think I was. like. 16--
I was about to commit suicide.

1230
00:57:35.703 --> 00:57:40.416
It was... I was being picked on
for being. you know. a big guy.

1231
00:57:40.499 --> 00:57:45.337
for being myself. and. you know.
being gay or whatnot.

1232
00:57:45.421 --> 00:57:47.923
and it was just all too much.

1233
00:57:48.007 --> 00:57:50.384
And...

1234
00:57:50.467 --> 00:57:54.263
it was that song. "My Life."
that helped me

1235
00:57:54.346 --> 00:57:56.557
to not actually
go through with that.

1236
00:57:56.640 --> 00:57:58.726
-MAN: That’s awesome.
-Yeah. -WOMAN: Beautiful.

1237
00:58:03.355 --> 00:58:05.566
MARY: I want the fans
to understand how important

1238
00:58:05.649 --> 00:58:07.359
they are to me.

1239
00:58:07.443 --> 00:58:09.695
’cause I didn’t think
I would even make it

1240
00:58:09.778 --> 00:58:12.239
to see this day
during that time.

1241
00:58:12.323 --> 00:58:14.241
I didn’t think I was gonna live.

1242
00:58:14.325 --> 00:58:16.035
♪ ♪

1243
00:58:16.118 --> 00:58:20.998
But something happened one day
when it was just too much.

1244
00:58:21.081 --> 00:58:24.752
I was sitting in my living room.
I had been up all night long.

1245
00:58:24.835 --> 00:58:28.297
And... it looked like
the window opening.

1246
00:58:28.380 --> 00:58:30.341
All these clouds came in.

1247
00:58:30.424 --> 00:58:32.843
I was just high out of my mind.

1248
00:58:34.470 --> 00:58:37.056
And my heart started racing.
and it was a Sunday morning.

1249
00:58:37.139 --> 00:58:39.225
I always feel strange
on a Sunday morning.

1250
00:58:39.308 --> 00:58:42.519
I always feel like God can see.
really see what I’m doing.

1251
00:58:42.603 --> 00:58:44.521
And I was like.
"I don’t want to do this.

1252
00:58:44.605 --> 00:58:46.607
I-I got to stop doing this."

1253
00:58:47.775 --> 00:58:49.568
Either you choose life
or you choose death.

1254
00:58:49.652 --> 00:58:53.489
and I chose life.
and it wasn’t even so much me

1255
00:58:53.572 --> 00:58:55.866
that was important to me.
it was my fans.

1256
00:58:55.950 --> 00:58:57.493
They bought the album.

1257
00:58:57.576 --> 00:58:59.245
They listened
to what I had to say.

1258
00:58:59.328 --> 00:59:01.497
They said. "Me. too. Mary."
and that was it.

1259
00:59:01.580 --> 00:59:03.499
That was the beginning
of our relationship.

1260
00:59:03.582 --> 00:59:05.668
and I think
that’s what-what I needed.

1261
00:59:05.751 --> 00:59:09.463
I needed someone to understand.

1262
00:59:11.131 --> 00:59:13.133
’Cause it seemed like
no one ever did.

1263
00:59:15.761 --> 00:59:20.099
They help me to sustain
and want to live

1264
00:59:20.182 --> 00:59:22.810
and survive on my journey.

1265
00:59:22.893 --> 00:59:26.480
We did something really great
and really powerful.

1266
00:59:26.563 --> 00:59:30.776
uh. inspiring each other.
by inspiring...

1267
00:59:30.859 --> 00:59:34.530
each other to want to live
to see another day.

1268
00:59:35.990 --> 00:59:40.244
So I just want people to just...
know that they-they’re not--

1269
00:59:40.327 --> 00:59:42.496
when you think you’re alone.
you’re not alone.

1270
00:59:44.164 --> 00:59:47.626
We-we soldiers out here.
all of us.

1271
00:59:47.710 --> 00:59:50.754
We got a job to fight. and
we all in the fight together.

1272
00:59:52.172 --> 00:59:54.300
